Initial thoughts

x1 is row identifier variable and can be dropped date - is month a possible predictor? Or create a season variable? total_bags looks to be sum of small + large + x_large; - check this with alias() to ensure no non-standard data/drop aliases total_volume looks to be sum(4046, 4225. 4770, total_bags) - again check with alias() before dropping aliases type - check how many distinct region - check how many distinct before deciding what to do with it

distinct(avocados, type)
distinct(avocados, region)

54 distinct regions: going to drop this variable

# Identify any aliased variables
alias(lm(average_price ~ ., 
         data = avocados))
Model :
average_price ~ x1 + date + total_volume + x4046 + x4225 + x4770 + 
    total_bags + small_bags + large_bags + x_large_bags + type + 
    year + region

No aliased variables? Seems odd when total_bags, total_volume appear to be made up of other variables

avocados %>% 
  mutate(bags = total_bags - small_bags - large_bags  - x_large_bags,
         vol = total_volume - x4046 - x4225 - x4770 - total_bags) %>% 
 filter(bags != 0)

Looks like problem is in rounding of number of decimal places. Just going to drop total_bags and total_volume variables. I experimented with rounding to 2dp but it still gave the same problem! Will ask about this on Monday.

avocados_trim <- avocados %>% 
  # Make "quarter" variable based on month
  mutate(
    quarter = as.factor(
      case_when(
        month(date) %in% 1:3 ~ "Q1",
        month(date) %in% 4:6 ~ "Q2",
        month(date) %in% 7:9 ~ "Q3",
        month(date) %in% 10:12 ~ "Q4"
      )
    ),
    year = as.factor(year)
    ) %>% 
  select(-c("x1", "date", "total_bags", "total_volume", "region"))

alias(lm(average_price ~ .,
         data = avocados_trim))
Model :
average_price ~ x4046 + x4225 + x4770 + small_bags + large_bags + 
    x_large_bags + type + year + quarter
avocados_trim %>% 
  ggpairs(progress = FALSE)

EXPLANATORY MODEL WORK:

glmulti_fit <- glmulti(
  average_price ~ .,
  data = avocados_trim,
  level = 2,
  minsize = 0,
  maxsize = -1,
  marginality = TRUE,
  method = "g",
  crit = bic,
  plotty = FALSE,
  report = TRUE,
  confsetsize = 100,
  fitfunction = lm
)
